 "draftNote": "1 of five queued off a bottom-two lane: Cuban Noobster (midlane→carry).",
 "coaching": {
  "headline": "Two won lanes (Murdock, GRIM) couldn't outpace a lost map — objectives 15-34 and towers 3-11 buried you.",
  "team": "Your bot side actually won: GRIM.exe carry was yours all game (11/4/8) and Murdock flipped the offlane his way from 10 minutes on (9/6/5). But the rest of the map cracked — Zinx mid was behind Renna at every check, Yin lost the jungle to Feng Mao, and you bled objectives 15-34 with towers 3-11. Two fixes carry over: itemize armor (Zinx and Yin both skipped it into a 3-physical comp, and their Sparrow hit 34k), and translate your won lanes into objective pressure before the enemy snowballs the neutral map.",
  "whatShiftedIt": "You won the fights you took bot but never grouped the lead into objectives — the enemy out-took neutrals and out-towered you 11-3. Convert won lanes into Prime/Fangtooth pressure as a five, and build the armor your matchup demanded.",
  "perPlayer": {
   "7c8ab99c-31c5-4ea5-a6fa-e0d6417c3f1b": "Murdock offlane, 9/6/5 — the Grux lane was even early (first checkpoint) and went yours from ~10 minutes on, which fits your win-rate read (you outscale Grux late). But your first real power spike (Vanquisher ~25m) didn't land until then, so the six deaths almost all come from contesting before you were online. Farm the even early window, then start fighting once Vanquisher is up.",
   "16f28434-561f-4f23-9454-40321f4a1ef3": "GRIM.exe carry, 11/4/8 and yours all game vs Sparrow — your best game on the team. With the lane that far ahead and your Imperator spike landing ~36m, the lead was there to close earlier; next time drag that won lane to the objective fights instead of farming it out while the map slips.",
   "a0c393cc-1437-4bdc-8168-64676ce2166c": "Zinx mid into Renna was theirs at every checkpoint (behind 5 through 30 minutes) and you only came online around your Oathkeeper spike ~19m — stop taking the 1v1 before then, just farm safe and roam to the bot lanes that were winning. You also ran no armor into a 3-physical enemy comp, so you folded fast in fights; buy it next time.",
   "10edbf65-457d-48d0-9151-9df5b4fcb40a": "Phase support, 0/6/20 — 20 assists and team-high mitigation is real frontline work, and your lane only slipped after the first checkpoint (yours at 5m, then theirs). With six deaths, watch the dive after minute 5: once Belica's side took over, ward deeper and peel from range rather than facechecking.",
   "a412baf3-dd17-4f89-8ecf-9d0704f3a79e": "Yin jungle, 6/11/6 with eleven deaths — the Feng Mao matchup was even at the first check then theirs the rest of the way, and you never hit a completed-item spike. On a near-first-time hero (5 games), play the early game safe, full-clear to catch up, and like Zinx you skipped armor into a 3-physical comp — that's a big chunk of the deaths."
  }
